{"type":"message","id":"5dbeee73","parentId":"7773c3d5","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:01:42.380Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the issue now. Looking at the hooks configuration in the config:\n\n```json\n\"hooks\": {\n  \"internal\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"entries\": {\n      \"session-memory\": { \"enabled\": true },\n      \"command-logger\": { \"enabled\": true },\n      \"self-improvement\": { \"enabled\": true },\n      \"context_hook\": { \"enabled\": true },\n      \"auto-score-classify\": { \"enabled\": true },\n      \"session-summary\": { \"enabled\": true }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe hooks are registered and enabled, but the critical issue is that they're under `internal.entries`. These appear to be the built-in internal hooks, not the ones in `/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/` directory.\n\nThe self-improvement handler.js at `/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/handler.js` is the external hook file, but the config registers it as `self-improvement` in `internal.entries`. \n\nI don't see a `bootstrap` event listener registered anywhere in the internal hooks. The session-summary and auto-score-classify hooks work because they're triggered by their respective events, but there's no `agent:bootstrap` event registered in the internal hooks configuration.\n\nSo the issue is clear: the handler.js file is loaded correctly and it filters for `event.type === 'agent' && event.action === 'bootstrap'`, but the OpenClaw gateway is never firing an `agent:bootstrap` event when /new is called. Without this event being triggered, the bootstrap hook has nothing to respond to.\n\nThe gateway would need to emit an `agent:bootstrap` event when starting a new session, but based on the current architecture, it seems like this event either doesn't exist or isn't being emitted. The gateway likely emits different events like `session:start` or `agent:start` instead.","thinkingSignature":"67aaa7c67ce06f505ace5fa5b35fa596b7032b8f7f3450d38c33d5a0f1b83ec6"},{"type":"text","text":"找到问题了。看 `config.json` 里的 hooks 注册：\n\n```json\n\"hooks\": {\n  \"internal\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"entries\": {\n      \"session-memory\": { \"enabled\": true },\n      \"self-improvement\": { \"enabled\": true },\n      \"auto-score-classify\": { \"enabled\": true },\n      \"session-summary\": { \"enabled\": true }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n这些是 **internal hooks**，但 `handler.js` 监听的是 `agent:bootstrap` 事件。问题在于：\n\n**Gateway 从未触发 `agent:bootstrap` 事件**\n\n`session-summary` 能work是因为它监听的是 `session:end`，Gateway 在 session 结束时主动发了事件。但 `/new` 触发的 bootstrap 逻辑——如果 Gateway 根本没有这个事件类型，handler.js 的 filter 就永远匹配不上。\n\n查一下 Gateway 的事件源：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t5gvyz02v34t_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"agent:bootstrap\\|bootstrap.*event\\|emit.*bootstrap\" /home/ai/.openclaw/v8/ --include=\"*.js\" -l 2>/dev/null | head -5"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t5gvyz02v34t_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"session:start\\|agent:start\\|new.*session\" /home/ai/.openclaw/v8/ --include=\"*.js\" -l 2>/dev/null | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":8145,"output":689,"cacheRead":18601,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27435,"cost":{"input":0.0024435,"output":0.0008267999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0011160599999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00438636}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776063674974,"responseId":"062bc7bab5c0770fa4da10cef9d8662e"}}
