{"type":"message","id":"290af26e","parentId":"a985a064","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:04:50.133Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `applyBootstrapHookOverrides` is called inside `resolveBootstrapFilesForRun`, which is called by `resolveBootstrapContextForRun`. And `resolveBootstrapContextForRun` is called from various places that need to build the bootstrap context for a run.\n\nThe key question is: **when is the `agent:bootstrap` event triggered?**\n\nLooking at the code flow:\n1. `resolveBootstrapContextForRun` is called when building context for a run\n2. It calls `resolveBootstrapFilesForRun`\n3. Which calls `applyBootstrapHookOverrides` \n4. Which triggers the `agent:bootstrap` event\n\nSo the `agent:bootstrap` event should be triggered when the bootstrap context is being built for a session run. This should happen when a new session starts or when a session needs its context rebuilt.\n\nBut the issue is: **the event is triggered asynchronously via `await triggerInternalHook(event)`, but the hook handlers in `/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/` are external hook files**. The internal hooks system (`registerInternalHook`) is for internal handlers, not external hook files.\n\nLet me check how external hooks (like the one in `/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/handler.js`) get registered and triggered. The HOOK.md says the hook fires on `agent:bootstrap`, but the external hook handler needs to be loaded somehow.\n\nLet me look at how external hooks are loaded and registered.","thinkingSignature":"7484320eced773d83d730624e1bc3586440b54187aa540f70d5844dcadb261d5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b44a12oj0r25_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"registerInternalHook\\|load.*hook\\|hook.*load\" /home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/ --include=\"*.js\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"node_modules\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":79554,"