{"type":"message","id":"b9f0e5b7","parentId":"49b153f1","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:09:33.342Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to go with the built-in hook mechanism. I need to:\n\n1. Check the current config.json hooks.internal.entries structure\n2. Modify the handler.js to be compatible with the internal hook format\n3. Add the entry to config.json\n\nLet me first look at the existing internal hooks to understand the pattern, then adapt the handler.js.\n\nThe current `hooks.internal.entries` in config.json has:\n```json\n\"self-improvement\": { \"enabled\": true },\n\"context_hook\": { \"enabled\": true },\n\"auto-score-classify\": { \"enabled\": true },\n\"session-summary\": { \"enabled\": true }\n```\n\nThe self-improvement hook is already registered and working. Let me check how it works as a reference.\n\nLooking at `/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/handler.js` - it's the self-improvement hook that injects during bootstrap. Let me look at how it's actually loaded.\n\nActually, wait. Looking at the config again, `self-improvement` is already registered as an internal hook. So the handler.js in the hooks folder IS being loaded somehow. Let me check the self-improvement.js file instead.\n\nActually looking at the hooks directory listing:\n- self-improvement.js\n- handler.js (same content?)\n\nLet me read self-improvement.js to see the pattern.","thinkingSignature":"63c85101fcbeac17aa50b629b3003c20513291ec5ef6a8ad7fd0cc14ad5781e2"},{"type":"text","text":"好，先看一下现有内置 hook 的实现模式：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_q4acubuykd3g_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/self-improvement.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":310,"cacheRead":82405,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82715,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0.000372,"cacheRead":0.0049442999999999996,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0053162999999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp