{"type":"message","id":"fadcdf73","parentId":"1fbd379f","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:09:36.748Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - `self-improvement.js` is empty or very short. Let me check the handler.js.","thinkingSignature":"97489907e0b84fa9e23311ea01791d88b0d51603eace20fd5c96e9b1f44427b5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_d62yubj65j5q_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/handler.js","limit":50}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":64123,"output":67,"cacheRead":18601,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82791,"cost":{"input":0.019236899999999998,"output":0.0000804,"cacheRead":0.0011160599999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.020433359999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776064173416,"responseId":"062bc9ac564e453c360a6b8570c788da"}}
{"type":"message","id":"afdc7c2a","parentId":"fadcdf73","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:09:36.813Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_d62yubj65j5q_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/**\n * Self-Improvement Hook for OpenClaw\n * \n * Injects:\n * 1. Self-improvement reminder\n * 2. MEMORY.md content (long-term memory)\n * 3. Latest session summaries (recent context)\n * \n * Fires on agent:bootstrap event before workspace files are injected.\n */\n\nimport fs from \"node:fs\";\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport os from \"node:os\";\n\nconst MEMORY_ROOT = path.join(\n  process.env.OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR || path.join(os.homedir(), \".openclaw\", \"workspace\"),\n  \"memory\"\n);\n\nconst SELF_IMPROVEMENT_REMINDER = `\n## Self-Improvement Reminder\n\nAfter completing tasks, evaluate if any learnings should be captured:\n\n**Log when:**\n- User corrects you → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- Command/operation fails → \\`.learnings/ERRORS.md\\`\n- User wants missing capability → \\`.learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md\\`\n- You discover your knowledge was wrong → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n- You find a better approach → \\`.learnings/LEARNINGS.md\\`\n\n**Promote when pattern is proven:**\n- Behavioral patterns → \\`SOUL.md\\`\n- Workflow improvements → \\`AGENTS.md\\`\n- Tool gotchas → \\`TOOLS.md\\`\n\nKeep entries simple: date, title, what happened, what to do differently.\n`.trim();\n\n// Read latest session summaries from memory/\nasync function getRecentSummaries() {\n  /** @type {string[]} */\n  const summaries = [];\n  try {\n    const files = await fs.promises.readdir(MEMORY_ROOT);\n    // Get .md files that contain \"summary\" or date pattern (most recent 3)\n    const summaryFiles = files\n      .filter(f => (f.includes('summary') || f.match(/\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}/)) && f.endsWith('.md'))\n      .filter(f => !f.startsWith('MEMORY'))\n\n[66 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776064176805}}
{"type":"message","id":"718f2bc8","parentId":"afdc7c2a","timestamp":"2026-04-13T07:09:50.424Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to understand how these hooks are actually registered and called. Let me look at the config to see how self-improvement is configured. Also let me look at how internal hooks work and how they're loaded.\n\nThe config shows:\n```json\n\"hooks\": {\n  \"internal\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"entries\": {\n      \"session-memory\": { \"enabled\": true },\n      \"command-logger\": { \"enabled\": true },\n      \"self-improvement\": { \"enabled\": true },\n      \"context_hook\": { \"enabled\": true },\n      \"auto-score-classify\": { \"enabled\": true },\n      \"session-summary\": { \"enabled\": true }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSo `self-improvement` is registered as an internal hook entry. But the handler.js in the hooks folder is not automatically loaded - it needs to be registered.\n\nLet me look at the hook loader to understand how hooks get loaded. The key is `registerInternalHook` which is called somewhere.\n\nActually, looking at the config, these entries reference something. The `self-improvement` key in `entries` must map to a hook that's registered somewhere. Let me see how that mapping works.\n\nActually I think the way it works is:\n1. The internal hooks are bundled in OpenClaw itself (like `self-improvement`, `auto-score-classify`, etc.)\n2. External hooks in `/home/ai/.openclaw/hooks/` are NOT automatically loaded\n\nSo the self-improvement hook that exists in config IS working, but it's a built-in/internal hook provided by OpenClaw, not the one in the hooks folder.\n\nLet me check if there's a `self-improvement.js` that actually has content, or if it's the one in `handler.js`.\n\nLet me also look at how the internal hooks are structured in the codebase. Let me search for where `self-improvement` is defined as an internal hook.","thinkingSignature":"5b349b6ac89e7c87778d8d6c7d5aa8b54694581f56d49cdcdcd15b623cf27f5e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_veqs8a0z7uyh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/bundled/ -name \"*.js\" | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_veqs8a0z7uyh_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /home/ai/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/bundled/"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":64653,"output":494,"cacheRead":18601,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":83748,"cost":{"input":0.0193959,"output":0.0005928,"cacheRead":0.0011160599999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02110476}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776064176815,"responseId":"062bc9af673f4e73117f3373434d32e9"}}
